App Deployment + CI/CD Pipeline

✅ Objectives:

    Create a simple static HTML app

    Setup GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline

    Automate web app deployment

🪜 Step-by-Step:
1. 🧾 Add a Web App
app/index.html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Azure Terraform Demo</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Welcome to My Azure Web App!</h1>
</body>
</html>

2. ⚙️ Enable Deployment Credentials in Azure

az webapp deployment user set --user-name <your-name> --password <your-password>

3. 🔐 Store Deployment Info in GitHub Secrets

Go to GitHub → Settings → Secrets → Add:

    AZURE_WEBAPP_NAME = my-webapp-demo

    AZURE_WEBAPP_PUBLISH_PROFILE = XML content from:

    az webapp deployment list-publishing-profiles \
      --name my-webapp-demo \
      --resource-group webapp-rg \
      --xml

4. 🪄 Setup GitHub Actions
.github/workflows/main.yml

name: Deploy Web App

on:
  push:
    branches: [ "main" ]

jobs:
  deploy:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Checkout repo
        uses: actions/checkout@v2

      - name: Deploy to Azure Web App
        uses: azure/webapps-deploy@v2
        with:
          app-name: ${{ secrets.AZURE_WEBAPP_NAME }}
          publish-profile: ${{ secrets.AZURE_WEBAPP_PUBLISH_PROFILE }}
          package: ./app

5. 🚀 Push & Trigger Pipeline

git add .
git commit -m "Day 2: Web app & CI/CD setup"
git push origin main

✔️ Your app will deploy automatically!
